The paper proposes a machine learning algorithm based on deep Q-networks to optimize replenishment decisions in a decentralized, multi-agent, cooperative problem. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The game theory aspect of the problem and the use of a decentralized multi-agent system suggest that it could also belong to the sub-categories of game theory (cs.GT) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with inventory optimization, which is a common problem in the field of operations research, suggesting that it could also belong to the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
